Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain. Pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, @Sugar Snap Peas{80%g} and @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

Drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Mango Chutney{40%g}, @Bulgogi Sauce{75%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the bulgogi beef and sugar snap peas.

Sprinkle over the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} to finish.

Enjoy!